{"title":"Spotted: Custom ENVE Aero Extensions For Pogačar’s Tour De France Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/spotted-custom-enve-aero-extensions-pogacar-tour-de-france/","date":1719257334000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-1536x1152.jpeg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions Pogacar Tour De France\" /></p>\n<p>Tadej Pogačar was recently spotted at the Giro d’Italia with some new ENVE Aero Extensions. Unlike what ENVE offers on its site, the sculpted sticks offer a slippery, custom look. While recently touring the ENVE Factory in breathtaking Ogden, Utah, we also spotted some new custom aero bars made expressly for Tadej Pogačar and the Tour de France.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Enve Aero Extensions on English side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(All photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor.com)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>ENVE Aero Extensions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Most of the riders from <a href=\"https://www.uaeteamemirates.com/\">UAE Team Emirates</a> are using the new ENVE Aero extensions, and we expect to see the entire tour squad using them in the coming weeks. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ENVE-Composites-factory-tour-ogden-utah-10-year-anniversary-nahbs-2017-60-600x400.jpg 600w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo: BikeRumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In Ogden, UT at the ENVE HQ last weekend for the<a href=\"https://enve.com/pages/grodeo\"> GRODEO</a>, we had some time to check out the factory and the beautifully built custom frames while also riding the ENVE GRODEO and short-track TT.<em> (*Side note – The GRODEO is one of the best gravel rides I’ve ever done – bucket list stuff for anyone curious).  </em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions For Pogacar engligh logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-For-Pogacar-engligh-logo-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Spotted on English Cycles </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The custom frames were all elegant, but one in particular had a unique piece of kit. Master builder Rob English’s custom-built <a href=\"https://www.englishcycles.com/\">English Cycles</a> steel TT bike sported the sought-after slippery ENVE TT extensions.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"English Cycles TT Bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/English-Cycles-TT-Bike--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>This is a steel bike! </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The ENVE TT extensions have everything a time trial rider needs to dial in their position. They boast lots of adjustability and molded forearm rests. They appear to be both comfortable and practical in the wind. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions Pogacar Tour De France\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tadej Pogačar Custom ENVE Aero Extensions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Later, in the custom fabrication corner of the ENVE Factory, we saw (and held) the ENVE TT extensions going straight to the Tour de France and Tadej Pogačar’s Colnago. The team at ENVE designed a custom ENVE Aero TT extension just for the yellow jersey hopeful. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions Pogacar Tour De France thumb\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-thumb-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions Pogacar Tour De France close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-close-up--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>What makes them different than what the team is riding? </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The ENVE TT extensions the team rides use an alloy plate for mounting and have adjustable extension sticks. This ensures that each rider can dial in their own ride to spec without needing a custom tune. The mounting hardware is standard, and the armrests are thicker to accommodate various forearm types.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions Pogacar Tour De France bolts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-bolts--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For Pogačar, the team put the already lightweight extensions on a tour diet and trimmed “lots of weight” from the package. <em>How?</em> The risers are carbon (not alloy), and the hardware is all titanium. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Custom Enve Aero Extensions Pogacar Tour De France shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Custom-Enve-Aero-Extensions-Pogacar-Tour-De-France-shifter-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Pogacar bars are not adjustable; they are bonded in place permanently. The top shifter portion is 3D printed to spec and sanded to perfection. The armrests are slightly thinner, but keep in mind the dimensions of the Pogačar arms. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Enve SES Prototype\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-SES-Prototype-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Is that a new ENVE Disc Wheel?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Those with sharp eyes will also notice a new <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-new-enve-ses-disc-wheel-is-tubeless-compatible-light-and-for-rim-or-disc-brakes/\">ENVE SES disc wheel</a>. All we know is that it’s tubeless, it’s “fast,” and optimized for wider tires. Keep a look out—more information will come as we get it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Enve Aero Extensions on English brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-brake--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Enve Aero Extensions on English side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-side--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"Enve Aero Extensions on English front of bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Enve-Aero-Extensions-on-English-front-of-bike--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Pogačar’s new TT bars are functional pieces of carbon art and craftsmanship. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out more made-in-the-USA carbon bits at<a href=\"https://enve.com/collections/road-components?tw_source=google&amp;tw_adid=&amp;tw_campaign=20547849738&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjwsuSzBhCLARIsAIcdLm6OjuF7xpfp1J6P960dgyvU-GeCA2Mks-tKEBKhaWBsv92Raea7vDsaAutlEALw_wcB\"> </a><em><a href=\"https://enve.com/collections/road-components?tw_source=google&amp;tw_adid=&amp;tw_campaign=20547849738&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjwsuSzBhCLARIsAIcdLm6OjuF7xpfp1J6P960dgyvU-GeCA2Mks-tKEBKhaWBsv92Raea7vDsaAutlEALw_wcB\">ENVE</a>.com</em><a href=\"https://enve.com/collections/road-components?tw_source=google&amp;tw_adid=&amp;tw_campaign=20547849738&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjwsuSzBhCLARIsAIcdLm6OjuF7xpfp1J6P960dgyvU-GeCA2Mks-tKEBKhaWBsv92Raea7vDsaAutlEALw_wcB\">. </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/spotted-custom-enve-aero-extensions-pogacar-tour-de-france/\">Spotted: Custom ENVE Aero Extensions For Pogačar’s Tour De France Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4b00fc491f4248525e477ffe87b5093bdbe88eb2c7c98baa0118258921b8f908","category":"Cycling"}